<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 04 at 4:25PM EDT  by NWS Wakefield</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern
Chesterfield, northeastern Nottoway and central Amelia Counties
through 530 PM EDT...
At 425 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Amelia Courthouse, moving northeast at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and locally heavy rainfall.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Mannboro, Amelia Courthouse, Chula, Spainville, Scotts Fork,
Winterpock, Earls, Winterham, Skinquarter, Maplewood, Fergusonville,
Clay Store and Denaro.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
